<subSubSection pageId="135" pageNumber="532" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="135.[169,1376,722,1582]" pageId="135" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,520,1353,1386]" pageId="135" pageNumber="532">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Lamotte’s White-toothed Shrew has a wide distribution, is considered common, and found in several nature reserves including Korup National Park in Cameroon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
